  "text_artifacts": {
    "cleaned_summary_text": "College of Engineering and Technology (Cairo)\n\nCollege of Engineering & Technology  Heliopolis\nomplementing the support of our students in facing the fierce global market and in conjunction with the accreditation of our programs from the most prestigious international bodies. The College of Engineering in Heliopolis has been keen to strengthen cooperation and partnership with prestigious universities around the world through the signing of several memoranda of understanding, student exchange agreements, and dual-degree agreements.\n\n1. Memoranda of Understanding\n\nThe College of Engineering and Technology has several MoU including the following universities:\n\nStaffordshire, Aston, and Manchester in the United Kingdom\nRovira I Virgili in Spain\nVirginia Tech and Sheridan in North America\nXiamen in China\n\n2. Exchange Programs\n\nOur students can also study one semester as an \"Exchange student\". Activities include educational tours, courses attendance, summer training and/or research activities. Attained courses in the partner university will be chosen according to availability under the guidance of the academic advisor. The following universities are among of our exchange programs:\n\nUniversity of Technology in Malaysia (UTM) in Malaysia\nUniversity of Northampton in UK\nUniversity of Central Lancashire (UCLAN) in UK"
  },
